HISTORY has been made! Banyana Banyana were crowned the Women’s Africa Cup of Nations (Wafcon) for the first time in history. The SA women’s team defeated the hosts Morocco 2-1 to win their first ever continental title. Hilda Magaia was the star of the show as she netted a brace in the second half of the match to help Desiree Ellis charges to win the match. Magaia broke the deadlock in the 63rd minute of the match. The skillful winger made it 2-0neight minutes later and that proved to be enough to earn Mzansi their first ever Awcon.  